subSubSection.paragraph:
Male abdomen (
Fig. 4D
) moderately broad; telson evenly rounded, length 0.63 times sixth segment; sixth segment 1.1 times longer than wide, lateral margins slightly convex; segments 3-5 progressively tapering, lateral margins of segment 4 and 5 straight; lateral margins of third segment strongly convex; first and second segments similar in width to third segment, but longitudinally very narrow. Male first gonopod almost straight in ventral view, apical section abruptly narrowed, set obliquely, tip corneous. Male second gonopod very short.
